    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><span class="" style="font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, mono;">int str_cmp(char *str1, char *str2)</span> should return the "lexicographical ordering" of the strings <span class="" style="font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, mono;">str1<span class="" style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"> </span></span>and <span class="" style="font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, mono;">str2</span>. Starting at the beginning of both strings, it returns 1 if the 0th character of str1 is greater than the 0th character of str2, or -1 if it's less. If they're equal, it looks at the 1st characters and does the same test, and so on. If it gets all the way to the end and the strings are identical throughout, it returns a 0. If the strings are identical at first, but then one string ends while the other doesn't, then the shorter string should be considered smaller (that is, you should return -1 if the first string is shorter, and 1 if the second one is).</p>]]></text>
